# OrthoReadics Privacy Policy

**Effective Date:** April 28, 2025

OrthoReadics (“we”, “our”, or “us”) built the OrthoReadics app. This Privacy Policy explains:

- **What data we collect**  
- **Why we collect it**  
- **How we store it**  
- **Your rights**

---

## 1. Data We Collect

**Profile data**  
• Name, email, institution, specialization, reading goals.  
• Papers read/presented, tags, notes, reminders.

**App usage**  
• Anonymous analytics (e.g. which feature tabs you open).  
• Crash reports (via Apple).

---

## 2. How We Use Your Data

- Provide and personalize the journal-club, library, and analytics features.  
- Save your reading progress and reminders locally.  
- Improve the app through anonymous usage statistics.  

> **We do NOT share** your personal data with third parties.

---

## 3. Storage & Security

- All data is stored locally on your device (in your own iCloud/Keychain if you choose).  
- We use industry-standard encryption when saving any files.

---

## 4. Your Rights

- You can **delete** your account at any time in Settings → Delete Account, which wipes all your data.  
- For questions or data-removal requests, email us at `your-support@yourdomain.com`.

---

## 5. Changes to This Policy

We may update this policy when adding features. We’ll update the “Effective Date” and post changes here.

---

© 2025 OrthoReadics. All rights reserved.
